paragraphs.title: Read in the Top County Jobs Analysis
paragraphs.text:
val bestCounties = spark.read.parquet("hdfs:///tmp/singlefiles/bestCounties.parquet")
//From each of the "best" countys, identify the industry with the highest employment level from the most recent quarter
val bestCountyIndus = spark.read.parquet("hdfs:///tmp/singlefiles/bestCountyIndus.parquet")

val mostRecentYr = bestCountyIndus.agg(max($"year").as("year"))
//Join the max year back into the data to filter for the most recent year (join allows for duplicates)
val bestCountyIndusMostRecentYear = bestCountyIndus.join(mostRecentYr,"year")
val mostRecentQtr = bestCountyIndusMostRecentYear.agg(max($"qtr").as("qtr"))
//Add a filter when "filtering" for the quarter value that removes the rows that have "Total" (since it's a summary for all industries) in the string
val bestCountyIndusMostRecentYrQtr = bestCountyIndusMostRecentYear.join(mostRecentQtr,"qtr").filter(!$"industry_title".contains("Total"))
bestCountyIndus.unpersist()
bestCountyIndusMostRecentYrQtr.cache()
bestCountyIndusMostRecentYrQtr.show(10)

paragraphs.title: Results -> Jobs + Storm Events View
paragraphs.text:
//Filter for the industries in each state with the highest employment
bestCountyIndusMostRecentYrQtr.createOrReplaceTempView("bestCountyIndusMostRecentYrQtr")

val bestCountiesWithIndus = spark.sql("SELECT * FROM bestCountyIndusMostRecentYrQtr A INNER JOIN (SELECT area_fips, max(Total_EmpLVL) Total_EmpLVL FROM bestCountyIndusMostRecentYrQtr GROUP BY area_fips) B ON A.area_fips = B.area_fips AND A.Total_EmpLVL = B.Total_EmpLVL")
bestCountiesWithIndus.persist()
bestCountiesWithIndus.show()

//Merge the two "bestCounties" DF's together to display the best county in the top ten states alongside their industry
val colsToRemove = Seq("month1_emplvl","month2_emplvl","month3_emplvl","disclosure_code","size_code","own_code")
val FinalCounties = bestCounties.join(bestCountiesWithIndus, bestCounties("Strm_FIPS_Code") === bestCountiesWithIndus("A.area_fips")).drop(colsToRemove:_*).drop($"A.Total_EmpLVL").drop($"A.area_fips")
FinalCounties.persist()
FinalCounties.show(false)

paragraphs.title: Future Improvements
paragraphs.text:
%md

+ Obviously, if this was a production system, I'd like to be able to set up a "pipeline" for this data to automagiccally updated as it's made available.
+ I really wanted to visualize this data to identify hotspots (using the lat and long data), but ran out of time to think about how to set this up.
+ Regarding visualization, I'd like to be able to view the charts via vegas at the very least, but kept running into memory issues

paragraphs.title: Plotting the Data
paragraphs.text:
val plotcounty = Vegas("Counties and their largest industry with fewest storm events").
  withDataFrame(FinalCounties).
  encodeX("CZ_NAME", Nom).
  encodeY("count", Quantitative).
  mark(Bar)
  
plotcounty.show
